&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frimley Health NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultants in Vascular Surgery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are pleased to advertise two replacement Consultant posts in Vascular Surgery. Both are full&lt;em&gt;-&lt;/em&gt;time with 10 Programmed Activities (PAs).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders will be expected to provide a full general and specialised vascular service, both elective and emergency, taking part in a 1:7 on call rota covering Frimley Park Hospital and the associated spoke vascular services at Heatherwood and Wexham Park Hospitals (part of Frimley Health Foundation Trust), The Royal Surrey County Hospital and North Hampshire Hospital. The job will involve elective sessions in one or more of the spoke hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The vascular department is a high performing service benefitting form a strong multidisciplinary team and purpose built facilities. The service is continually evolving and hence the job plan is subject to change to meet the demands of the service. It is anticipated that in the near future, there will be further expansion of the service in collaboration with Ashford and St Peter’s Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested applicants are very welcome to contact the following via the Frimley Park Hospital: &lt;br /&gt;Ian Laidlaw, Chief of Service, General Surgery 07768 094724 &lt;br /&gt;David Gerrard, Lead Consultant in Vascular Surgery 07727204386&lt;br /&gt;Sally Vaughan, Associate Director of Surgery 07768845644.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 20th November 2020&lt;br /&gt;Interview date: 27th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
